title: Tangled Webs: Ch 10 and 11
body:
IT’S FINALLY FINISHED! :-O

Excerpt from Chapter 11: Looking to the Future

          “So you were trying to protect me?” Tony said incredulously; Loki was relieved to find that Stark sounded amused rather than offended.  “Like a princess in a tower?”

           “Hardly that,” Loki protested.  “But Earth needs defenders, as many as it can marshal.  You have a penchant for trying to solve problems all by yourself.”

           “So you were trying to protect me from myself,” Stark concluded, and Loki had no words to argue with that, so he shrugged.  Stark exhaled long and low, giving Loki a narrow eyed look, but didn’t pursue the point. “But it feels like you sort of side-stepped my question, so I’ll ask it more plainly: are you trying to take over the world again?”

           “No.  I’m trying to help you take over the world.”

           Stark blinked at him for a long time, stunned, before he finally said, “What?”

summary: Peter: You know, Tony, I like Father's Day. Not everyone in life has one but I had three. Of course, I still love Uncle Ben and...
body:
Peter: You know, Tony, I like Father’s Day. Not everyone in life has one but I had three. Of course, I still love Uncle Ben and Dad, but lately you have been the one who was here. On this day you and I as never before are close, and I can tell you about everything that worries me. I recently started dating MJ. She is great. And yes, I entered the MIT, can you imagine? All thanks to the lessons with you. I … You know, I miss.

Petet, looking at a Tony’s grave: Happy Father’s Day, Dad.

title: El último primer beso
body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2yMmPia

by MonnAmouur

“Thanos observó todo cuanto se abría paso delante suyo. Todos quienes se interponían entre su sueño, y él. Sonrió con orgullo. Como su más fiel allegado solía pronunciar… Todos aquellos delante de él, eran sus hijos. Y, aunque fuese en la muerte, serían parte de la historia de piedad y misericordia más esperada de todos los tiempos.
—¿Vale tanto, hijo mío? ¿Lo suficiente como para morir por él?
Los ojos del castaño han comenzado a llenarse de lágrimas tan pronto como ha hablado. Le toma apenas unos segundos responder.
—Ninguna otra vida vale más para mí que la suya…”

James B. Barnes x Tony Stark

blog.title: Tony Stark Fanfic Prompts
blog.description:
Basically a bunch of prompts about Tony Stark/the Avengers. 
(please write me some fics)

body:
Tony Stark Prompt:

(No Powers AU)

The Stark family was well-known, ridiculously so. They were constantly in the news and tabloids, as if it was their personal goal to remain in the eyes of the public. So it was really no surprise that young Tony Stark was raised in the spotlight.

But Tony hated it.

He would have been perfectly comfortable living in a remote cabin in the woods, thank you very much. So he runs away. Far away, into the back country deep in the midwest. He just didn’t expect to fall in love with the ridiculously attractive cowboy/girl(s) that lived there.
